IF it were up to Rhulani Mokwena, individual awards in football would be scrapped. The Mamelodi Sundowns coach has weighed in on the raging debate, sparked by the PSL Coach of the Month. Together with co-coach Manqoba Mngqithi, Mokwena was snubbed for the best coach award at the virtual ceremony on Sunday. But the league winning coach has seemingly not taken the judges’ decision to overlook his hard work to heart. “I’ve always retained the stance that football should not have individual awards. It’s my opinion,” he said. “No individual wins a game in football. You can put the coach on the touchline, but without the quality of the players, without the work ethics, the ability to express themselves and help the team win, you can’t win matches.        